President Donald Trump has proclaimed November 2017 as National Veterans and Military Families Month in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the significant contributions made by American service members, their families, and their loved ones. It highlights the sacrifices and hardships endured by military families, including frequent relocations and separations from loved ones. The proclamation also mentions the reforms and improvements made at the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to provide better service for veterans. The president encourages all communities and sectors of society to acknowledge and honor the service, sacrifices, and contributions of veterans and military families.